You should install the following tools: php 7.*, nginx and mysql
0. First of all
  0.1 sudo apt-get update

1. Installing php 7.*
  1.1 sudo apt-get install php-fpm php-mysql
  1.2 For security, you should disable the cgi.fix_pathinfo option at php.ini file. Example:
    1.2.1 sudo vi /etc/php7.0/fpm/php.ini
      1.2.1.1 cgi.fix_pathinfo=0
  1.3 Restart the php processor
    1.3.1 sudo systemctl restart php7.0-fpm

2. Installing Mysql
  2.1 sudo apt-get install mysql-server

3. Installing nginx
  3.1 sudo apt-get install nginx
  3.2 Configure the default file
    3.2.1 sudo vi /etc/nginx/sites-available/default
      3.2.1.1 change / uncomment the following parts:
        root path_to_public;

        index index.php index.html index.htm index.nginx-debian.html;

        location ~ \.php$ {
            include snippets/fastcgi-php.conf;
            fastcgi_pass unix:/run/php/php7.0-fpm.sock;
        }

        location ~ /\.ht {
            deny all;
        }
    3.2.2 Test your modifications
      3.2.2.1 sudo nginx -t
    3.2.3 Restart the service
      3.2.3.1 sudo systemctl reload nginx
    3.2.4 Test at browser
      3.2.4.1 http://localhost:80
